# Thermometer Service

A temporary Kafka consumer service that acts as a virtual thermometer device, collecting temperature data from a Kafka stream for dashboard visualization.

## Overview

This service listens to a Kafka topic, simulates a thermometer device by consuming temperature events, and provides data collection capabilities for a .NET MVC dashboard application.

## Features

- Kafka stream consumer
- Temperature data collection
- Dashboard-ready data format
- Real-time monitoring

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Kafka broker running
- .NET runtime (for dashboard integration)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository
2. Configure Kafka connection settings
3. Run the service

### Configuration

Set your Kafka broker connection and topic details in the configuration file.

## Usage

The service will automatically begin listening to the configured Kafka topic and collecting temperature data.

## Notes

This is a temporary service designed as a prototype for the thermometer device simulation.
